Reasoning: The paper discusses the tracking of users' browsing habits on the web, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and privacy (cs.CY). The analysis of user-generated data and the use of social and physical connections suggest a focus on social computing (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SD). The discussion of advertising networks and user experience points towards human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
